<h1 id="wb-cont">Introduction</h1>
	<section class="alert alert-info">
  	<h3>The Safe Travel Planner is getting a facelift!</h3>
  		<p>We are currently updating this online tutorial to make it more interactive and even more interesting. However during that time, it remains accessible in its current format. You may earn yourself a Safe Travel Planner certificate from Global Affairs Canada by simply getting informed about safe travel abroad!</p>
  		<p>Please note that the information found in this tool applies to travel in normal circumstances and not during the COVID-19 pandemic. It does not contain references to the current travel restrictions in place. </p>
  		<p>We would also like to take this opportunity to inform you that Global Affairs Canada offers free live bilingual webinars to education institutions and members of the travel industry. These webinars provide information on: </p>
  		<ul>
  			<li>Travel advice and advisories</li>
  			<li>Consular services in the context of COVID-19</li>
  			<li>Help abroad</li>
  			<li>TravelSmart and ArriveCAN apps</li>
  		</ul>
  		<p>To arrange a webinar for your organization - <a href="mailto:outreach.sensibilisation@international.gc.ca">outreach.sensibilisation@international.gc.ca</a>

	</section>


